Updated November     pm





Matt Brown  Cal State Fullerton Sports Media Stock Photo

Cal State Fullerton golf concluded its season with a seventhplace finish in the Big West Championships Tuesday PERIOD The Titans dropped two spots from fifthplace which they occupied when play ended Tuesday PERIOD

UC Santa Barbarawhich hosted the tournamentwon the threeday competition with a 12under par  and will move on to one of six NCAA Regionals PERIOD

Titans star Jack Ireland missed the tournament with an injury but Matt Wilson picked up the slack as the top finisher for Fullerton closing out the tournament in a sevenway tie for eighth place with a 1under par  PERIOD

Wilson finished even at par on the final day of the tournament to jump four spots from his roundone finish of twelfth place PERIOD The sophomore held on with steady play as he also finished even at par on the first day of the tournament while finishing with a 1under par  in the second day of play PERIOD

Wilson was the only Titan to finish in the top  PERIOD

As a team the Titans finished with a 7over par  one stroke behind UC Irvine for the sixth spot PERIOD

CSUF finished the first round of the tournament in eighth place with a 12over par  with Matt Wilson leading the way PERIOD

The Titans came back on the links on Tuesday in the second round with their best performance of the tournament moving up three spots to finish the day in fifth place with an 8under par  PERIOD Matt Murphy was the standout performer for the Titans on day two with a 7under par  PERIOD

Fullerton couldnt live up to its daytwo performance in the third and final round of the tournament finishing with a 3over par  which pushed the Titans back two spots to finish seventh out of nine teams PERIOD

Mark Cobey Michael Sharkey and Wilson all finished day three even at par to lead CSUF but it wasnt enough to keep the Titans near the top of the team leaderboards PERIOD

With the season now over the Titans look forward to the abundance of players returning for next year PERIOD Only Martin Manalo and Murphy will not be back with the team next season PERIOD
